1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,920
<i>How many more people</i>
<i>are going to have to die for this?</i>

2
00:00:04,879 --> 00:00:07,841
<i>I'll do what I promised you I would.</i>
<i>Do you understand?</i>

3
00:00:07,924 --> 00:00:09,259
<i>Let's go!</i>

4
00:00:09,342 --> 00:00:11,302
- [IAN]<i> Bro!</i>
- [GUNSHOTS]

5
00:00:12,303 --> 00:00:13,388
<i>Ian!</i>

6
00:00:13,471 --> 00:00:14,764
<i>Ian!</i>

7
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:16,307
[FURIOUS SCREAM]

8
00:00:16,391 --> 00:00:18,935
<i>My condolences for what happened</i>
<i>to your brother.</i>

9
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:20,562
<i>We can't leave the island yet.</i>

10
00:00:20,645 --> 00:00:23,314
<i>I have to get back at them</i>
<i>for my brother's death.</i>

11
00:00:23,398 --> 00:00:25,150
<i>I'm going to kill Liam and Olsen.</i>

12
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:29,738
<i>Why are the men I deployed</i>
<i>at the dock not answering?</i>

13
00:00:29,821 --> 00:00:32,365
<i>Maybe our comms can't reach that far.</i>

14
00:00:32,866 --> 00:00:36,619
[LUCAS] <i>I can go make sure</i>
<i>our plan is going smoothly.</i>

15
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:39,372
<i>That no VIP guest escapes.</i>

16
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:42,792
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [CHAINS RATTLING]

17
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:45,587
- [OFFICER]<i> Go to the other boat. Hurry!</i>
- [WENDY SCREAMS]

18
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:46,755
<i>Get down!</i>

19
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:49,174
[GUNFIRE, PEOPLE SCREAMING]

20
00:00:50,925 --> 00:00:52,260
<i>Cariaso!</i>

21
00:00:52,844 --> 00:00:54,471
[FIN SCREAMS, GROANS]

22
00:01:00,685 --> 00:01:01,686
Emil?

23
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:02,937
Emil.

24
00:01:03,021 --> 00:01:04,022
Emil!

25
00:01:04,105 --> 00:01:06,357
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

26
00:01:06,441 --> 00:01:07,776
Well?

27
00:01:07,859 --> 00:01:09,319
Are you the boss or not?

28
00:01:09,402 --> 00:01:11,196
Why won't they listen to you?

29
00:01:11,946 --> 00:01:14,574
<i>We won't tell anyone.</i>
<i>We don't even know who you are.</i>

30
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:16,493
[EMIL] <i>Really?</i>

31
00:01:17,327 --> 00:01:18,495
<i>Huh?</i>

32
00:01:18,578 --> 00:01:21,122
[MAGNUS] <i>I told you,</i>
<i>we'll pay whatever you ask.</i>

33
00:01:21,206 --> 00:01:23,875
<i>One hundred million. Two hundred million.</i>

34
00:01:23,958 --> 00:01:26,211
<i>Please, spare my family.</i>

35
00:01:26,294 --> 00:01:28,004
<i>So you're a good father.</i>

36
00:01:30,089 --> 00:01:31,966
<i>But a good husband?</i>

37
00:01:32,801 --> 00:01:33,843
<i>I don't think so.</i>

38
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:38,348
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

39
00:01:38,431 --> 00:01:40,433
<i>But he hurt you.</i>

40
00:01:42,977 --> 00:01:44,979
<i>You feel bad for this man?</i>

41
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:46,231
[LOUD THWACK]

42
00:01:48,358 --> 00:01:50,485
<i>Who are you talking to?</i>

43
00:01:50,568 --> 00:01:52,112
<i>You don't know who she is?</i>

44
00:01:53,321 --> 00:01:55,907
<i>You got amnesia or something? Huh?</i>

45
00:01:56,407 --> 00:01:58,451
Who exactly is this Emil?

46
00:02:00,286 --> 00:02:02,831
Why does it seem like he has
a personal grudge against us?

47
00:02:02,914 --> 00:02:04,415
Against my husband and my son?

48
00:02:04,499 --> 00:02:07,877
He said your family wronged him.

49
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:09,546
Particularly your husband.

50
00:02:09,629 --> 00:02:11,881
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

51
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:14,050
What can you tell me about Emil?

52
00:02:14,884 --> 00:02:17,220
He was my colleague once, a cop like me.

53
00:02:18,847 --> 00:02:21,099
But he fell into drugs.

54
00:02:21,182 --> 00:02:24,561
He owes me his life and freedom.

55
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:34,279
<i>Does the name Smile ring a bell?</i>
<i>She's one of our staff.</i>

56
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:37,073
<i>She is Emil's daughter.</i>

57
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:43,913
Break this lock. Open it!

58
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:46,166
- Why?
- Enough talk!

59
00:02:46,249 --> 00:02:47,542
Just do it!

60
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:49,836
[LOCK SLAMS]

61
00:02:49,919 --> 00:02:53,298
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

62
00:02:53,381 --> 00:02:55,466
What are you looking for?
Whose locker is this?

63
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:58,469
This belonged to one of my staff,
who turned out to be Emil's daughter.

64
00:02:58,553 --> 00:03:02,015
- What?
- She posed as one of our resort staff.

65
00:03:02,098 --> 00:03:03,433
Her real name's Leni.

66
00:03:03,516 --> 00:03:05,727
- The same person Liam shot?
- Yes.

67
00:03:05,810 --> 00:03:07,645
That's his only issue with your family?

68
00:03:07,729 --> 00:03:11,441
But he was saying something
about your husband, Magnus.

69
00:03:11,524 --> 00:03:17,739
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

70
00:03:33,713 --> 00:03:40,637
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

71
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:15,588
[WAVES LAPPING IN THE DISTANCE]

72
00:04:20,176 --> 00:04:27,183
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

73
00:04:29,018 --> 00:04:30,895
[GULL CRIES]

74
00:04:39,570 --> 00:04:40,738
[SNIFFS SHARPLY]

75
00:04:44,284 --> 00:04:47,287
[MUSIC INTENSIFYING]

76
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:52,292
So where do we go now?

77
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:54,585
We've got no police backup now.

78
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:56,296
Where's Areza?

79
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:59,465
Why didn't any reinforcements arrive?

80
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:01,801
Lieutenant Areza hasn't returned.

81
00:05:03,052 --> 00:05:05,263
We have no idea where he is.

82
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:09,267
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

83
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:11,853
Did Greta say where she was going?

84
00:05:11,936 --> 00:05:15,732
She wanted to look for you both.

85
00:05:15,815 --> 00:05:17,775
Magnus, she just bolted.

86
00:05:18,943 --> 00:05:21,404
Liam, we tried to stop your mother.

87
00:05:21,487 --> 00:05:23,406
But she wouldn't let us.

88
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:24,532
What?

89
00:05:24,615 --> 00:05:25,825
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

90
00:05:25,908 --> 00:05:28,453
There's so many of you here,
but you didn't stop her?

91
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:34,042
Seriously?! You could've dragged her if
you had to to make sure she stayed.

92
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,418
[WENDY] Liam!

93
00:05:36,044 --> 00:05:39,088
The cops tried to hold her back,

94
00:05:39,172 --> 00:05:41,215
but she lost her temper.

95
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:43,426
So we let her be.

96
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:45,344
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

97
00:05:45,428 --> 00:05:47,138
<i>Think about your own safety too.</i>

98
00:05:47,221 --> 00:05:48,306
<i>Really?</i>

99
00:05:48,389 --> 00:05:52,018
<i>Don't you want me to be left here</i>
<i>so you can have my family to yourself?</i>

100
00:05:52,101 --> 00:05:53,102
[WENDY] <i>That's enough!</i>

101
00:05:55,396 --> 00:05:58,232
Liam, your mother wanted
to be left behind.

102
00:05:58,983 --> 00:06:00,318
But, ma'am,

103
00:06:00,985 --> 00:06:04,072
wasn't it you who said
we should just leave her?

104
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:08,159
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

105
00:06:08,242 --> 00:06:09,243
You said that?

106
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:13,581
And all of you did nothing?

107
00:06:13,664 --> 00:06:15,041
Seriously, Liam?

108
00:06:15,792 --> 00:06:17,502
Are you for real?

109
00:06:18,252 --> 00:06:20,171
So we're playing the blame game now?

110
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:22,173
So much has already happened!

111
00:06:24,008 --> 00:06:27,178
Why don't you try thinking of ways
to get off this island first?

112
00:06:27,261 --> 00:06:32,225
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

113
00:06:38,397 --> 00:06:39,315
[DADO] Boss.

114
00:06:41,484 --> 00:06:42,693
They're gone.

115
00:06:42,777 --> 00:06:45,279
The hostages have escaped.

116
00:06:45,988 --> 00:06:48,116
I'm sure some cops are still around.

117
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:51,119
No way they all crammed into
one speedboat.

118
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:55,581
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

119
00:06:55,665 --> 00:06:56,874
The senator's son?

120
00:06:57,792 --> 00:07:00,419
Negative, boss.
We still haven't found him.

121
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:04,549
We need to find the hostages.

122
00:07:04,632 --> 00:07:06,425
Especially the senator's son.

123
00:07:07,009 --> 00:07:10,471
As long as he knows
we're holding his son hostage,

124
00:07:10,555 --> 00:07:14,642
he won't let the police storm the island.

125
00:07:14,725 --> 00:07:16,644
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

126
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:18,396
That'll be our trump card.

127
00:07:18,479 --> 00:07:19,814
[DADO] Yes, sir.

128
00:07:20,356 --> 00:07:21,315
[LUCAS] Boss Emil.

129
00:07:22,483 --> 00:07:26,362
The senator can't find out
we don't have his son anymore.

130
00:07:30,908 --> 00:07:32,660
- Sir.
- Go on.

131
00:07:32,743 --> 00:07:36,914
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

132
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:39,834
[SIGHING DEEPLY]

133
00:07:43,087 --> 00:07:44,130
[GRUNTS]

134
00:07:47,258 --> 00:07:48,468
[HUFFS]

135
00:07:50,178 --> 00:07:51,637
When you recruited Emil,

136
00:07:51,721 --> 00:07:53,598
how did you get him to say yes?

137
00:07:54,932 --> 00:07:56,642
I knew he was strapped for cash,

138
00:07:56,726 --> 00:07:59,270
and this deal meant millions.

139
00:07:59,353 --> 00:08:01,314
Why wouldn't he jump at it?

140
00:08:02,064 --> 00:08:03,399
What if this is the reason?

141
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:04,609
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

142
00:08:04,692 --> 00:08:06,903
How is he related to that woman?

143
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:08,529
Ayen?

144
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:11,240
She's his eldest daughter.

145
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:12,950
You know her?

146
00:08:15,119 --> 00:08:17,997
She was once my husband's mistress.

147
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:19,415
That's it?

148
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:22,001
Are they still seeing each other?

149
00:08:22,084 --> 00:08:23,544
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

150
00:08:23,628 --> 00:08:25,546
So where is Ayen now?

151
00:08:26,422 --> 00:08:27,632
I don't know.

152
00:08:28,966 --> 00:08:30,718
All I care about

153
00:08:30,801 --> 00:08:34,931
is that no one finds out
I planned all of this.

154
00:08:35,014 --> 00:08:38,392
They'll use it to take revenge on us.
To destroy us.

155
00:08:38,476 --> 00:08:40,603
Why would he take revenge though?

156
00:08:40,686 --> 00:08:43,606
It's his daughter's fault too
for getting involved with your husband.

157
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:45,650
I don't know!

158
00:08:46,984 --> 00:08:50,196
This all needs to stop!

159
00:08:51,155 --> 00:08:52,448
I'll handle Emil.

160
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:53,741
Jericho,

161
00:08:53,824 --> 00:08:56,285
Emil needs to be gone.

162
00:08:58,246 --> 00:09:00,164
If he gets the money,

163
00:09:00,831 --> 00:09:04,001
he'll just use it to get back at us.

164
00:09:04,961 --> 00:09:06,170
Without him,

165
00:09:06,254 --> 00:09:09,549
we stand to gain a whole lot more.

166
00:09:09,632 --> 00:09:11,759
We'll split the money between us.

167
00:09:12,593 --> 00:09:14,178
Hang on, Greta.

168
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:15,763
[HUFFS]

169
00:09:15,846 --> 00:09:18,599
We had a clear deal about the split.

170
00:09:19,433 --> 00:09:20,434
[GRETA SCOFFS]

171
00:09:20,518 --> 00:09:22,395
You plan to keep your word?

172
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:28,276
How long have you even known him
to trust him like that?

173
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:30,820
He is indebted to me,

174
00:09:30,903 --> 00:09:32,697
and he must honor that debt.

175
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:33,906
Honor?

176
00:09:34,490 --> 00:09:37,201
You really think that lunatic
would honor anything?

177
00:09:37,285 --> 00:09:39,328
Don't you see?

178
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:40,913
He doesn't listen to you!

179
00:09:40,997 --> 00:09:42,957
He disrespects you!

180
00:09:43,624 --> 00:09:45,334
He's going to betray you!

181
00:09:45,418 --> 00:09:48,963
If I were you, I'd strike first.

182
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:51,299
Those men of his…

183
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:53,134
Did you recruit them too?

184
00:09:53,217 --> 00:09:54,844
I control them.

185
00:09:54,927 --> 00:09:59,807
Then tell them not to hurt
my husband and my son.

186
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:03,477
No more killings.
No more people getting hurt.

187
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:06,689
No one?

188
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:08,816
What do you mean?

189
00:10:08,899 --> 00:10:11,360
What about the thing
you asked me to do before?

190
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:13,946
[GRETA] <i>Jericho.</i>

191
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:16,866
<i>Any updates? Are your men ready?</i>

192
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:18,534
<i>They all are.</i>

193
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:21,662
<i>They're ready</i>
<i>to go to the island tomorrow.</i>

194
00:10:21,746 --> 00:10:23,706
<i>Did you explain the plan clearly?</i>

195
00:10:23,789 --> 00:10:25,291
[JERICHO] <i>Of course.</i>

196
00:10:25,374 --> 00:10:27,001
<i>Go to the island,</i>

197
00:10:27,084 --> 00:10:29,045
<i>secure the hostages,</i>

198
00:10:29,128 --> 00:10:32,340
<i>and threaten them</i>
<i>to make them pay a ransom.</i>

199
00:10:32,965 --> 00:10:34,842
<i>Once my people get the money,</i>

200
00:10:34,925 --> 00:10:36,135
<i>they'll escape.</i>

201
00:10:37,094 --> 00:10:38,846
<i>No one will get harmed.</i>

202
00:10:38,929 --> 00:10:40,556
[GRETA] <i>Except for one person.</i>

203
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:43,100
<i>If she fights back,</i>

204
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:45,645
<i>let your men handle her.</i>

205
00:10:45,728 --> 00:10:48,064
<i>What if they kill her?</i>

206
00:10:48,147 --> 00:10:50,274
<i>That's not my fault.</i>

207
00:10:50,358 --> 00:10:51,651
<i>She was the one who fought back.</i>

208
00:10:53,819 --> 00:10:57,156
Is that plan still on, Greta?

209
00:10:58,032 --> 00:11:01,452
Just make sure to prioritize

210
00:11:01,535 --> 00:11:04,038
my family's safety.

211
00:11:04,121 --> 00:11:07,667
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

212
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:13,214
Enough with the arguing.

213
00:11:13,881 --> 00:11:15,091
It's not helping.

214
00:11:17,093 --> 00:11:18,511
Olsen.

215
00:11:18,594 --> 00:11:20,596
Try to understand Liam.

216
00:11:21,972 --> 00:11:23,307
[OLSEN] Grandpa,

217
00:11:23,391 --> 00:11:25,559
Mama already told him

218
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:27,478
that it was Ma'am Greta
who wanted to stay.

219
00:11:28,187 --> 00:11:30,356
But he's still blaming Mama.

220
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:34,402
Son, if you think about it,
I'm also at fault.

221
00:11:34,485 --> 00:11:36,112
It's not your fault, Ma.

222
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:38,739
Are you going to blame yourself again?

223
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:41,867
Ma'am Greta has been
taking advantage of you all this time.

224
00:11:42,493 --> 00:11:44,370
That's why you had to go to jail.

225
00:11:44,453 --> 00:11:47,498
Now, you'll let Liam
treat you harshly too?

226
00:11:47,581 --> 00:11:49,625
Son, that's enough.

227
00:11:49,708 --> 00:11:51,544
- Enough.
- [OLSEN] What?

228
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:52,920
Ma, Grandpa.

229
00:11:53,712 --> 00:11:55,589
Are we just going to let them

230
00:11:56,757 --> 00:11:58,509
step on us?

231
00:12:00,261 --> 00:12:01,554
I'm done with that, Ma.

232
00:12:03,055 --> 00:12:04,682
You know, I hope…

233
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:08,686
you understand where I'm coming from, Ma.

234
00:12:11,856 --> 00:12:13,232
[OLSEN] You know,

235
00:12:13,315 --> 00:12:15,067
when I was a kid…

236
00:12:15,776 --> 00:12:17,778
[BREATH QUIVERS]

237
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:19,572
When I lost you,

238
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:23,784
people began to look down on me.

239
00:12:25,035 --> 00:12:26,787
Do you know what they call me?

240
00:12:28,497 --> 00:12:29,874
"Criminal's son."

241
00:12:29,957 --> 00:12:34,003
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

242
00:12:34,086 --> 00:12:36,338
But I knew you weren't a criminal.

243
00:12:37,882 --> 00:12:39,467
It hurt.

244
00:12:42,303 --> 00:12:44,013
I'm not blaming you, Ma.

245
00:12:46,182 --> 00:12:47,475
It just hurt.

246
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:49,935
Then my…

247
00:12:50,603 --> 00:12:54,648
my father-- I've never met him.

248
00:12:55,399 --> 00:12:59,153
So other people would say that
he probably went to jail too.

249
00:12:59,778 --> 00:13:01,155
That he was also a criminal.

250
00:13:04,658 --> 00:13:06,285
That's why I worked hard, Ma.

251
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:09,413
That's why, someday,

252
00:13:10,789 --> 00:13:12,833
I want to become an important person.

253
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:14,084
Someone…

254
00:13:16,253 --> 00:13:18,380
they can't belittle.

255
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:22,259
So they can't treat me like trash.

256
00:13:25,346 --> 00:13:28,807
So I hope you understand

257
00:13:28,891 --> 00:13:31,727
if I get hurt when they look down on me.

258
00:13:33,729 --> 00:13:35,981
Of course, it hurts more

259
00:13:37,441 --> 00:13:39,735
if you're the one
being treated like that, Ma.

260
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:42,613
[WENDY SOBS, SNIFFLES]

261
00:13:45,115 --> 00:13:46,867
Son, I'm sorry.

262
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:48,744
You don't have to apologize, Ma.

263
00:13:48,827 --> 00:13:51,539
I didn't know
you went through all of that.

264
00:13:51,622 --> 00:13:53,290
I'm not asking for an apology.

265
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:54,583
[WENDY SNIFFLES]

266
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:56,293
[WENDY EXHALES SHARPLY]

267
00:13:57,920 --> 00:13:59,463
I just want you

268
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:02,007
to understand me.

269
00:14:03,551 --> 00:14:07,137
I hope you understand, especially now.

270
00:14:07,805 --> 00:14:09,765
[OLSEN] I won't let anything bad
happen to you, Ma.

271
00:14:09,848 --> 00:14:15,604
We now know Ma'am Greta's true colors.

272
00:14:16,313 --> 00:14:17,940
Right?

273
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:21,443
So we shouldn't take their side.

274
00:14:21,527 --> 00:14:22,903
Olsen.

275
00:14:23,988 --> 00:14:26,031
We're not picking sides.

276
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:29,243
What I'm trying to say is, grandson,

277
00:14:29,326 --> 00:14:31,370
you're not thinking straight.

278
00:14:31,453 --> 00:14:33,581
- [OLSEN SCOFFS]
- You need to understand that!

279
00:14:34,415 --> 00:14:36,000
Grandpa, I'm your grandson.

280
00:14:36,083 --> 00:14:38,627
- I know. But learn how to understand.
- [WENDY] Enough.

281
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,546
Why does it seem like you value Liam more?

282
00:14:42,673 --> 00:14:44,884
- [WENDY] Pa, stop it.
- You don't get how I feel.

283
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:47,219
Pa, no. Let him be.

284
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:52,892
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

285
00:14:52,975 --> 00:14:56,020
[JERICHO] Emil's already deviated
far away from our plan.

286
00:14:57,187 --> 00:14:58,355
Don't worry.

287
00:14:58,439 --> 00:14:59,940
I'll fix this.

288
00:15:01,692 --> 00:15:02,610
Stay here.

289
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:05,112
Make sure of it, Jericho.

290
00:15:05,195 --> 00:15:07,156
You already owe me a lot.

291
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:09,366
You messed up because of Emil.

292
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:11,744
That's why he needs to go.

293
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:13,621
Can you remove him from the plan?

294
00:15:13,704 --> 00:15:16,832
Or are you his lapdog,
ready to follow all his orders?

295
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:19,126
I'll handle him.

296
00:15:19,209 --> 00:15:20,836
Where's the money?

297
00:15:21,962 --> 00:15:23,297
They have it.

298
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:25,132
How much do they have?

299
00:15:25,215 --> 00:15:27,843
Adding up all they got,

300
00:15:27,927 --> 00:15:29,929
including money and jewelry,

301
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:31,972
it's about 300 million.

302
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:35,059
Do you know where they're keeping it?

303
00:15:35,893 --> 00:15:37,186
Why?

304
00:15:37,269 --> 00:15:39,563
I need you to do one more thing.

305
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:44,360
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

306
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:52,952
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

307
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:54,244
[OFFICER] Sebastian.

308
00:15:55,996 --> 00:15:56,956
Yes, sir?

309
00:15:57,039 --> 00:15:58,832
[KEYS JINGLE]

310
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:01,961
[METAL CLANKS, CREAKS]

311
00:16:04,463 --> 00:16:06,840
[METAL CLANKS]

312
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:13,263
- Where are you taking me?
- Just come with me.

313
00:16:14,932 --> 00:16:19,061
[METAL CLANKING]

314
00:16:23,649 --> 00:16:24,858
You're free.

315
00:16:38,706 --> 00:16:40,374
[PHONE BEEPS, LINE RINGING]

316
00:16:40,916 --> 00:16:42,501
Senator.

317
00:16:42,584 --> 00:16:45,879
[LUCAS] <i>Did you accomplish our objective?</i>

318
00:16:46,714 --> 00:16:48,716
I have your brother with me.

319
00:16:53,512 --> 00:16:54,680
[DARK MUSIC STING]

320
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:01,812
Thank you, Lucas.

321
00:17:01,895 --> 00:17:03,939
Homer. [CHUCKLES]

322
00:17:04,565 --> 00:17:06,233
We agreed

323
00:17:06,316 --> 00:17:08,277
that you'll give me my son back.

324
00:17:08,902 --> 00:17:10,612
I will, Senator.

325
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:12,031
Just be patient.

326
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:14,408
<i>I want to talk to Macky.</i>

327
00:17:14,491 --> 00:17:17,327
Let your son rest, Senator.

328
00:17:17,411 --> 00:17:19,705
[LUCAS] You'll reunite with him tomorrow.

329
00:17:19,788 --> 00:17:23,000
I'll bring him to you myself.

330
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:25,377
I said I want to talk to my son!

331
00:17:25,461 --> 00:17:28,672
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

332
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:30,674
He's far from where I am.

333
00:17:30,758 --> 00:17:32,092
[SCOFFS]

334
00:17:32,801 --> 00:17:34,720
I won't let your brother go

335
00:17:34,803 --> 00:17:37,639
until I'm sure that my son is alive.

336
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:40,392
We agreed to make
the exchange on the spot.

337
00:17:40,476 --> 00:17:43,020
My son for your brother!

338
00:17:44,938 --> 00:17:47,441
Why can't you understand?
I already told you--

339
00:17:47,524 --> 00:17:49,359
Where's my son?!

340
00:17:49,443 --> 00:17:51,236
Give me back my son!

341
00:17:53,614 --> 00:17:56,992
- [PANTING]
- [DOOR OPENS]

342
00:18:02,039 --> 00:18:09,046
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

343
00:18:23,519 --> 00:18:25,395
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

344
00:18:25,479 --> 00:18:27,815
What happened to my son?

345
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:30,651
If you won't let me talk to him,

346
00:18:30,734 --> 00:18:32,486
I'll kill your brother!

347
00:18:32,569 --> 00:18:34,571
[MEN GRUNTING]

348
00:18:34,655 --> 00:18:36,532
[GUNSHOTS]

349
00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:38,492
Homer.

350
00:18:38,575 --> 00:18:39,409
<i>Homer!</i>

351
00:18:39,493 --> 00:18:41,286
Don't try to follow me!

352
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:42,830
[GUNSHOT]

353
00:18:42,913 --> 00:18:45,457
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

354
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:47,167
- [HOMER GRUNTS]
- [GUNSHOT]

355
00:18:51,713 --> 00:18:57,636
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

356
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:08,814
Damn you, Senator!

357
00:19:08,897 --> 00:19:11,150
<i>If something bad happens to my brother,</i>

358
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,777
<i>I will kill your entire clan!</i>

359
00:19:18,699 --> 00:19:25,706
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

360
00:19:31,712 --> 00:19:32,629
[SMACKS]

361
00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:38,969
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

362
00:19:39,928 --> 00:19:42,598
[HORN HONKING]

363
00:19:43,265 --> 00:19:46,351
[HORN HONKING]

364
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:48,061
[GROANS]

365
00:20:00,532 --> 00:20:02,034
Leni, dear.

366
00:20:02,951 --> 00:20:04,536
Just hang in there for a bit more.

367
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:07,164
We're going to leave soon.

368
00:20:07,247 --> 00:20:08,373
Pa…

369
00:20:08,457 --> 00:20:10,209
Let's stop this, Pa.

370
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:12,586
Let's just leave now.

371
00:20:12,669 --> 00:20:14,504
We can't do that.

372
00:20:16,298 --> 00:20:19,676
Dado is still looking
for the other hostages.

373
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:22,095
We're going to catch all of them again.

374
00:20:22,721 --> 00:20:25,307
We don't need them, Pa.

375
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:27,851
You already got a lot of money, right?

376
00:20:27,935 --> 00:20:30,229
[EXHALES SHARPLY] Isn't it enough?

377
00:20:30,312 --> 00:20:32,731
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

378
00:20:32,814 --> 00:20:35,651
From the start, you knew

379
00:20:35,734 --> 00:20:38,445
that this wasn't just about money.

380
00:20:38,528 --> 00:20:40,572
It's for your sister.

381
00:20:41,615 --> 00:20:45,994
I'll do everything I can
so we can all be together again.

382
00:20:48,622 --> 00:20:51,750
That's why I need to find Magnus Roja.

383
00:20:52,626 --> 00:20:56,046
I'm sure he knows where Ayen is.

384
00:20:58,966 --> 00:21:00,300
[EMIL] Leni?

385
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:02,386
Leni, dear!

386
00:21:02,469 --> 00:21:05,889
Leni? Leni! Leni!

387
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:07,307
Leni!

388
00:21:08,141 --> 00:21:09,935
What…? Leni!

389
00:21:10,018 --> 00:21:14,690
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

390
00:21:15,732 --> 00:21:17,192
[EMIL] <i>Leni! Wake up!</i>

391
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:19,861
[MAGNUS] <i>I'll talk to the leader</i>
<i>of the hostage takers.</i>

392
00:21:19,945 --> 00:21:21,947
<i>You know they will kill you.</i>

393
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:25,325
<i>You said that Olsen's father</i>
<i>was already dead.</i>

394
00:21:25,409 --> 00:21:26,785
<i>Is he really dead already?</i>

395
00:21:26,868 --> 00:21:28,495
<i>Let's go. Come on!</i>

396
00:21:29,621 --> 00:21:32,082
<i>When those animals find us,</i>
<i>let's lead them here.</i>

397
00:21:32,165 --> 00:21:33,959
<i>They'll die for sure</i>
<i>if they fall down there.</i>

398
00:21:34,042 --> 00:21:35,752
- [SCREAMS]
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]

399
00:21:37,087 --> 00:21:38,630
[KEEPS SCREAMING]

400
00:21:38,714 --> 00:21:40,632
<i>- Son, this is my battle.</i>
<i>- This is our battle.</i>

401
00:21:40,716 --> 00:21:42,384
<i>This is our family's battle.</i>
